le-linear-regression-mlr"></span><h2 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_1-0" class=3D"comp=
 mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class=
=3D"mntl-sc-block-heading__text text-title-300"> What Is Multiple Linear Re=
gression (MLR)? </span> </h2>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_2-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-ht=
ml mntl-sc-block-html"> Multiple linear regression (MLR), also known simply=
 as multiple regression, is a statistical technique that uses several expla=
natory variables to predict the outcome of a response variable. The goal of=
 MLR is to model the <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/l/linear=
relationship.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-t=
ype=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">linear relationship</a> between the=
 explanatory (independent) variables and response (dependent) variables. In=
 essence, multiple regression is the extension of ordinary least-squares (O=
LS) <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/r/regression.asp" data-co=
mponent=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data=
-ordinal=3D"2">regression</a> because it involves more than one explanatory=
 variable.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_3-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ads=
lot mntl-block"></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_4-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
