-callout theme-whatyouneedtoknow" data-tracking-id=3D"mntl-sc-block-callout=
" data-tracking-container=3D"true"> <h3 class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-ca=
llout__heading">Key Takeaways</h3>
<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__body"><ul><li>Multiple linea=
r regression (MLR) is a statistical technique that uses several explanatory=
 variables to predict the outcome of a response variable.</li><li>Multiple =
regression is an extension of linear (OLS) regression that uses just one ex=
planatory variable.</li><li>MLR is used extensively in econometrics and fin=
ancial inference.</li><li>Multiple regressions are used to make forecasts, =
explain relationships between financial variables, and test existing theori=
es.</li></ul></div>
</div>
