<span class=3D"heading-toc" id=3D"toc-what-multiple-linear-regression-mlr-c=
an-tell-you"></span><h2 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_8-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-bloc=
k finance-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class=3D"mntl-sc-b=
lock-heading__text text-title-300"> What Multiple Linear Regression (MLR) C=
an Tell You </span> </h2>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_9-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-ht=
ml mntl-sc-block-html"> Simple linear regression is a function that allows =
an analyst or statistician to make predictions about one variable based on =
the information that is known about another variable.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_10-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_11-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Linear regression can only be used when one has tw=
o continuous variables=E2=80=94an independent variable and a dependent vari=
able. The independent variable is the parameter that is used to calculate t=
he dependent variable or outcome. A multiple regression model extends to se=
veral explanatory variables.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_12-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"><div id=3D"mid-ad-table-group_1-0" class=3D"comp mid-ad-ta=
ble-group mid-bankingtable mntl-block rate-table-mid dynamic-inline" data-r=
ight-rail-index=3D"3"></div></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_13-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The MLR model is based on the following assumption=
s:
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_14-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<ul id=3D"mntl-sc-block_15-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
html mntl-sc-block-html">
<li>There is a <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/l/linearrelati=
onship.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D=
"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">linear relationship</a> between the depen=
dent variables and the independent variables</li>
<li>The independent variables are not too highly <a href=3D"https://www.inv=
estopedia.com/terms/c/correlation.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=
=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"2">correlated</a=
> with each other</li>
<li>y<sub>i</sub> observations are selected independently and randomly from=
 the population</li>
<li>Residuals should be <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/n/nor=
maldistribution.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" dat=
a-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"3">normally distributed</a> with a =
mean of 0 and <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/v/variance.asp"=
 data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLi=
nk" data-ordinal=3D"4">variance</a> <em>=CF=83</em></li>
</ul>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_16-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_17-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block=
-callout mntl-sc-block-universal-callout theme-important finance-sc-block-c=
allout--generic" data-tracking-id=3D"mntl-sc-block-callout" data-tracking-c=
ontainer=3D"true"> <h3 class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__heading">I=
mportant</h3>
<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__body"><p>MLR assumes there i=
s a linear relationship between the dependent and independent variables, th=
at the independent variables are not highly correlated, and that the varian=
ce of the residuals is constant.</p></div>
<div id=3D"finance-sc-block-callout__icon-container_1-0" class=3D"comp fina=
nce-sc-block-callout__icon-container mntl-block"><svg class=3D"icon finance=
-sc-block-callout__icon--important ">
<use xmlns:xlink=3D"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href=3D"#finance-sc=
-block-callout__icon--important" href=3D"#finance-sc-block-callout__icon--i=
mportant"></use>
</svg></div></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_18-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/=
c/coefficient-of-determination.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"=
inlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">coefficient of de=
termination</a> (R-squared) is a statistical metric that is used to measure=
 how much of the variation in outcome can be explained by the variation in =
the independent variables. R<sup>2</sup> always increases as more predictor=
s are added to the MLR model, even though the predictors may not be related=
 to the outcome variable.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_19-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_20-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Thus, R<sup>2</sup> by itself can't be used to ide=
ntify which predictors should be included in a model and which should be ex=
cluded. R<sup>2</sup> can only be between 0 and 1, where 0 indicates that t=
he outcome cannot be predicted by any of the independent variables, and 1 i=
ndicates that the outcome can be predicted without error from the independe=
nt variables.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_21-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_22-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> When interpreting the results of multiple regressi=
on, beta coefficients are valid while holding all other variables constant =
("all else equal"). The output from a multiple regression can be displayed =
horizontally as an equation or vertically in table form.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_23-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<span class=3D"heading-toc" id=3D"toc-example-of-how-to-use-multiple-linear=
-regression-mlr"></span><h2 id=3D"mntl-sc-block_24-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc=
-block finance-sc-block-heading mntl-sc-block-heading"> <span class=3D"mntl=
-sc-block-heading__text text-title-300"> Example of How to Use Multiple Lin=
ear Regression (MLR) </span> </h2>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_25-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> As an example, an analyst may want to know how the=
 movement of the market affects the price of ExxonMobil (XOM). In this case=
, the linear equation will have the value of the S&amp;P 500 index as the i=
ndependent variable, or predictor, and the price of XOM as the dependent va=
riable.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_26-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_27-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> In reality, <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.co=
m/terms/s/stepwise-regression.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"i=
nlineLink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">multiple factors p=
redict the outcome</a> of an event. The price movement of ExxonMobil, for e=
xample, depends on more than just the performance of the overall market.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_28-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_29-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Other predictors, such as the price of oil, intere=
st rates, and the price movement of oil <a href=3D"https://www.investopedia=
.com/terms/f/futures.asp" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink=
" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">futures</a>, can affect the=
 price of Exxon Mobil (<a href=3D"https://www.investopedia.com/markets/quot=
e?tvwidgetsymbol=3Dxom" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineLink" =
data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"2">XOM</a>) and the stock prices=
 of other oil companies. To understand a relationship in which more than tw=
o variables are present, MLR is used.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_30-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_31-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> MLR is used to determine a mathematical relationsh=
ip among several random variables. In other words, MLR examines how multipl=
e independent variables are related to one dependent variable.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_32-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_33-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Once each of the independent factors has been dete=
rmined to predict the dependent variable, the information on the multiple v=
ariables can be used to create an accurate prediction of the level of effec=
t they have on the outcome variable. The model creates a relationship in th=
e form of a straight line (linear) that best approximates all the individua=
l data points.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_34-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_35-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Referring to the MLR equation above, in our exampl=
e:
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_36-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<ul id=3D"mntl-sc-block_37-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-=
html mntl-sc-block-html"> <li>y<sub>i</sub> =3D dependent variable=E2=80=94=
the price of XOM</li><li>x<sub>i1</sub> =3D interest rates</li><li>x<sub>i2=
 </sub>=3D oil price</li><li>x<sub>i3 </sub>=3D value of S&amp;P 500 index<=
/li><li>x<sub>i4</sub>=3D price of oil futures</li><li>B<sub>0</sub> =3D y-=
intercept at time zero</li><li>B<sub>1</sub> =3D regression coefficient tha=
t measures a unit change in the dependent variable when x<sub>i1</sub> chan=
ges=E2=80=94the change in XOM price when interest rates change</li><li>B<su=
b>2</sub> =3D coefficient value that measures a unit change in the dependen=
t variable when x<sub>i2</sub> changes=E2=80=94the change in XOM price when=
 oil prices change</li>
</ul>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_38-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_39-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The least-squares estimates=E2=80=94B<sub>0</sub>,=
 B<sub>1</sub>, B<sub>2</sub>=E2=80=A6B<sub>p</sub>=E2=80=94are usually com=
puted by statistical software. As many variables can be included in the reg=
ression model in which each independent variable is differentiated with a n=
umber=E2=80=941,2, 3, 4...p.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_40-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_41-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block=
-callout--note finance-sc-block-callout mntl-sc-block-universal-callout the=
me-note finance-sc-block-callout--generic" data-tracking-id=3D"mntl-sc-bloc=
k-callout" data-tracking-container=3D"true"> <h3 class=3D"mntl-sc-block-uni=
versal-callout__heading">Fast Fact</h3>
<div class=3D"mntl-sc-block-universal-callout__body"><p>Multiple regression=
 can also be non-linear, in which case the dependent and&nbsp;independent v=
ariables&nbsp;would not follow a straight line.<br></p></div>
<div id=3D"finance-sc-block-callout__icon-container_2-0" class=3D"comp fina=
nce-sc-block-callout__icon-container mntl-block"><svg class=3D"icon finance=
-sc-block-callout__icon--fast-fact ">
<use xmlns:xlink=3D"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href=3D"#finance-sc=
-block-callout__icon--fast-fact" href=3D"#finance-sc-block-callout__icon--f=
ast-fact"></use>
</svg></div></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_42-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> The multiple regression model allows an analyst to=
 predict an outcome based on information provided on multiple explanatory v=
ariables.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_43-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_44-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> Still, the model is not always perfectly accurate,=
 as each data point can differ slightly from the outcome predicted by the m=
odel. The residual value, E, which is the difference between the actual out=
come and the predicted outcome, is included in the model to account for suc=
h slight variations.
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_45-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
slot mntl-block"></div>
<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_46-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-h=
tml mntl-sc-block-html"> We ran our XOM price regression model through a st=
atistics computation software. It returned this output:
</p>
<div id=3D"mntl-sc-block_47-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-ad=
